act with a variety of integral groups and to elicit and retain their support.</li><li class=\"\">Corporate Social Responsibility can be perceived as the voluntary integration of social and environmental concerns into business operations and interactions with stakeholders.</li><li class=\"\">Employees of different disciplines will have to manage stakeholders in their endeavours.</li><li class=\"\">Stakeholder management evolved as a tenet of corporate social responsibility and is underpinned by ethical, social, and economic considerations. It aims to describe, understand, analyse and manage stakeholders.</li><li class=\"\">Three approaches are useful for dealing with stakeholders–strategic approach, multi-fiduciary approach and stakeholder synthesis approach. A stakeholder management approach takes many factors into account, for example, moral, political, technological and economic interests.</li><li class=\"\">Max Clarkson has proposed seven principles of stakeholder management.</li></ul></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li></ul>\n","\n<ul class=\"maintree ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-valid ng-isolate-scope ui-sortable ng-not-empty\"><li id=\"LSrmc\" data-space=\"\" full-editor=\"\" class=\"component list header, listed   ui-resizable\"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div class=\"head editable ng-pristine ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None ng-touched\" ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" spellcheck=\"false\"><h4><b>Lesson Summary</b></h4></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li><li id=\"DmlWZ\" data-space=\"\" full-editor=\"\" class=\"component list paragraph, listed   ui-resizable\"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" class=\"editable p-asset ng-pristine ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope None ng-touched ng-not-empty\" spellcheck=\"false\"><b>The key points that were covered in this module are:</b></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li><li id=\"ZSfPi\" data-space=\"\" full-editor=\"\" class=\"component list list-item, listed selected-class   ui-resizable border\"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" class=\"list-item editable ng-pristine ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None ng-touched\" spellcheck=\"false\"><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"\">A stake is an interest or a share in an agreement, while a stakeholder is an individual with a stake—types of stakeholders– internal and external stakeholders.</li><li class=\"\">Most commonly identified stakeholders include customers, employees, investors, suppliers and vendors, communities and government.</li><li class=\"\">Stakeholder management is about maintaining relationships between an organisation and its stakeholders. It requires an organisation to interact with a variety of integral groups and to elicit and retain their support.</li><li class=\"\">Corporate Social Responsibility can be perceived as the voluntary integration of social and environmental concerns into business operations and interactions with stakeholders.</li><li class=\"\">Employees of different disciplines will have to manage stakeholders in their endeavours.</li><li class=\"\">Stakeholder management evolved as a tenet of corporate social responsibility and is underpinned by ethical, social, and economic considerations. It aims to describe, understand, analyse and manage stakeholders.</li><li class=\"\">Three approaches are useful for dealing with stakeholders–strategic approach, multi-fiduciary approach and stakeholder synthesis approach. A stakeholder management approach takes many factors into account, for example, moral, political, technological and economic interests.</li><li class=\"\">Max Clarkson has proposed seven principles of stakeholder management.</li></ul></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li></ul>\n","\n<ul class=\"maintree ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-valid ng-isolate-scope ui-sortable ng-not-empty