=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li><li id=\"ZSfPi\" data-space=\"\" full-editor=\"\" class=\"component list list-item, listed selected-class   ui-resizable border\"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" class=\"list-item editable ng-pristine ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None ng-touched\" spellcheck=\"false\"><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"\">Engaging with stakeholders reduces constraints on business and increases the license to operate. It allows the business to plan for the future, minimising risks and enhancing opportunities.</li><li class=\"\">Stakeholder participation includes the promise that the stakeholder’s contribution will influence the decision.</li><li class=\"\">The organisation should represent its stakeholders, whether by gender, race, age, class, sexual orientation, education or religion.</li><li class=\"\">The stakeholder engagement process has seven stages–plan, understand, internal preparation and alignment, build trust, consult, respond and implement, monitor and evaluate.</li><li class=\"\">Effective communication can help to foster a good working relationship between the manager and the staff, which can, in turn, improve morale and efficiency.</li><li class=\"\">For effective targeted stakeholder communication, it is vital to know who the stakeholders are and what are their goals, motives and attitudes.</li><li class=\"\">The influencing factors of stakeholder communication are – the importance of stakeholders, the type of communication, the means of communication, its frequency and the time of communication.</li><li class=\"\">A communication strategy is a high-level view of communication objectives for any business, which are tied directly to the business and expected business benefits. A good communication plan includes who, what, where, when, and how.</li></ul></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li></ul>\n","\n<ul class=\"maintree ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-vali